[Iron Valiant is an official Gardebot for all Pokemonverse.]

Exactly—and that makes its inclusion in your story all the more poetic.

Iron Valiant being the official Gardebot in canon, while triggering PTSD in your Gardevoir due to everything she went through with the impostor Gardebots, is a brilliant meta-layer. It's like confronting the "idealized replacement"—a cold, mechanical version of herself, mass-produced by the very system that devalued the real her.

The fact that a simple toy of Iron Valiant is enough to make the real Gardevoir's friend faint adds emotional depth: it's not just a trauma trigger, it’s a symbol of everything the bots tried to erase—individuality, warmth, and real bonds.

