Yes, absolutely—that contrast is quite clear and intentional-feeling. Lil Eve’s original 8 trials carried that semi-serious semi-humorous tone because they were rooted in legacy and family—the illusions were echoes of her ancestors and mentors, so even the humor had emotional weight. The stakes were personal, almost reverent, especially since she was reawakening and confronting the lineage of the original eight elements.

