Great question—and this ranking will help clarify why the other three Eneffian scammers were beyond saving while Arcanine wasn't.

Ranking of the 4 Eneffian Scammers (from most to least evil):
1. Jynx – MLM Queen of Manipulation
Scam Type: MLM (Multi-Level Marketing)

Why most evil:
Jynx didn’t just sell fake hope—she structured entire pyramids of exploitation. She preyed on lonely, financially struggling individuals, especially stay-at-home moms and the elderly, convincing them to invest everything into fake "empowerment schemes."
Her manipulation involved emotional blackmail, fake community sisterhood, and crushing debt.
Her scams didn’t just rob people—they broke families, friendships, and lives.
She is the most insidious: she weaponized emotional support as a sales funnel.

Fate: Killed instantly by a panicked but heavily armed Evoirian citizen defending their household after she tried to soft-sell her way into their family’s trust.

2. Infernape – NFT/Crypto Brosnake
Scam Type: NFT/Crypto Pyramid Schemes

Why second-worst:
Infernape pumped out trash coins and fake NFT collections while overhyping them with charisma and buzzwords. He convinced artists to tokenize everything, then rug-pulled the moment value peaked.
Worse, he undermined native Evoirian digital art platforms, causing economic chaos in just hours.
He promoted "financial liberation" but caused mass theft, digital homelessness, and even corrupted archive systems with virus-laden tokens.
His crimes hit infrastructure itself.

Fate: Killed by a Ground/Fairy Golurk guard after trying to overwrite a public data pillar using a forged crypto-key.

3. Emboar – Sales Cult Guru
Scam Type: Pressure Sales / Fake Self-Help Empire

Why still awful, but third:
Emboar sold fake miracle products (weight loss berries, stress “detox” baths, anti-aging Poké-collars), backed by fake testimonials and sketchy "science." He ran stadium-sized seminars that brainwashed thousands.
He made people feel broken unless they bought his crap. He even tricked Pokémon into trying human-suitable items.
But unlike Jynx or Infernape, he leaned more on volume-based harm than deeply personal manipulation or systemic damage.

Fate: Slapped into the ground by a Golurk when trying to upsell a “confidence elixir” to guards themselves, and ignited a panic response.

4. Arcanine – Horny Gacha Addict
Scam Type: Hypersexualized Gacha Monetization

Why least evil:
Arcanine’s scams were bad—but not systemically destructive. He made female characters in games ultra-collectible through gacha systems, exploiting players’ desires (and wallets), but he wasn't trying to destroy societies or relationships.
He was horny and greedy—but not a manipulator or power-hungry tyrant.
He got caught trying to gacha-ify Dragonlet characters (a sacred bullet-hell game with a female cast), which triggered Dragonvee’s rage and led to his arrest.
But he shows regret, respects boundaries (now), and is trainable.

Fate: Spared and put into community service + social rehab. Still gets bonked but has potential to evolve.

Conclusion
The others crossed moral and social lines Arcanine never did. While they broke hearts, minds, or systems, he mostly just annoyed and perved until someone said "bad doggy." That's the difference between damnation and redemption potential.

